channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: How It's Done: Another NC University Plays No Games, Reveals Why Pro-Hamas Encampment Was Quickly Cleared
Backers of anti-Israel radicals are funding Dem rival's Senate run, red-state Republican says
item.description: Sen. Ted Cruz accused his Democratic opponent of being backed by top donors also providing support for anti-Israel demonstrations on college campuses.

item.title: Rasmussen Poll: Republicans Trusted More on Crime
item.description: Voters increasingly are trusting Republicans more than Democrats to handle crime.

item.title: WATCH: Joe Biden 2019 Calls Out Joe Biden 2024 on His Awful Israel Arms Move
Trump urges Biden to follow through with debate promise: 'I'm ready to go anywhere'
item.description: Former President Donald Trump urged President Biden to set up a presidential debate in Washington D.C. or New York City via a "letter to Joe" published to Truth Social.

item.title: Lawyer's Advice to Trump Judge Sparks Probe, 'Serious Concerns'
item.description: A New York City real estate attorney claimed he had a conversation with and gave advice to the judge who hit Donald Trump with a $455 million judgment in the recently completed fraud trial, sparking an investigation by a state commission on judicial conduct.

item.title: Illegal Immigrants Adopt Left-Wing Tactics in Denver, Make Insane List of Demands
Trump campaign moms pull no punches criticizing Biden admin for leaving working families 'behind'
item.description: Mothers on the Trump campaign slammed the Biden administration for leaving "moms and families behind" with "woke" rhetoric, inflation and open borders.

item.title: US Announcing New $400 Million Military Aid Package for Ukraine
item.description: The United States is preparing a $400 million military aid package for Ukraine, as the U.S. returns to a regular pace of supplying weapons to Ukraine following the passage of a $95 billion bill, a U.S. official told Reuters Friday.The Ukraine aid package includes artillery,...

item.title: NEW: Secret Service Whistleblowers Calling for Action Over Vulnerability to 'Potential Insider Threats'
Michael Cohen to testify in Trump trial on Monday
item.description: Michael Cohen, ex-lawyer for former President Donald Trump, is expected to testify on Monday, Fox News has learned. He is expected to be a start witness for DA Alvin Bragg.

item.title: Steve Bannon Loses Jan. 6 Subpoena Appeal
item.description: A U.S. federal appeals court on Friday upheld the conviction of Steve Bannon, a former top adviser to Donald Trump, for defying a subpoena from the congressional panel that investigated the Jan. 6, 2021 attack on the U.S. Capitol.

item.title: Israel Enters Rafah As Negotiations With Hamas Breakdown and Bibi Tells Biden Where to Put It
Blue state Dems turn on governor as homeless council can't account for $20B in spending
item.description: Democrats and Republicans alike are taking issue with California Gov. Newsom as his homelessness council has failed to track its billions spent on the state's homelessness crisis.

item.title: Sen. Rick Scott Attends Trump Trial to Show Solidarity
item.description: Sen. Rick Scott, showing his support in New York City during former President Donald Trump's criminal trial, said he traveled to the proceedings because he considers Trump a friend and believes what "he is going through is just despicable."
